devdoc.details: Implement functionalities of Oracle. Other functionalities (e.g.: open/close seaosn) are implemented by keepers

aggregate(uint16,bytes32).details: Aggregate a `severity` from all submissions. Rule benefit insurees: if 50% (roundup) of total submissions is >= totD2 + totD3 + totD4 then severity is severity which got the most number of submissions between D2,D3 & D4 Else severity which got most number of submissions between D0 & D1 Emits a {SeverityAggregated} event. Pays out the keeper for its job Requirements: - the caller must be keeper. - the season must be in closed state - contract must have enough balance to pay oracle - the keeper cannot trigger aggregation twice for this `season` + `region`

closeSeason(uint16).details: Close a `season`. Emits a {SeasonClosed} event. Pays out the keeper for its job Requirements: - the caller must be keeper - the season must be opened - contract must have enough balance to pay keepers

getSubmission(uint16,bytes32,address).details: Retrieve a `severity` for a given `region` and `season` , provided by `oracle`.

getSubmissionNumberForSeverity(uint16,by.details: Retrieve number of submissions for a given `region` and `season` and `severity`.

getSubmissionTotal(uint16,bytes32).details: Retrieve total submissions for a given `region` and `season`.

getSubmitterAt(uint16,bytes32,uint256).details: Retrieve submitter  for a given `region` and `season` at a given `index`.

openSeason(uint16).details: Open a `season`. Emits a {SeasonOpen} event. Pays out the keeper for its job Requirements: - the caller must be keeper. - the season must be in default state - contract must have enough balance to pay keepers

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setGateKeeper(address).details: Allow to change dynamically access control contract (GateKeeper)

params._gateKeeper: gateKeeper address Requirements: - only owner can change the reference of GateKeeper - ensure that it impelments the right interface

submit(uint16,bytes32,uint8).details: Submit a `severity` for a given `season` + `region`. Emits a {SeveritySubmitted} event. Pays out the oracle for its job Requirements: - the caller must be oracle. - the season must be in open state - contract must have enough balance to pay oracle - the oracle cannot submit twice for this `season` + `region` - severity code must be valid

switchContractOff().details: If the contract is active then stop it and emit a {ContractOff} event. Requirements: - the caller must be root admin.

switchContractOn().details: If the contract is stopped then active it and emit a {ContractOn} event. Requirements: - the caller must be root admin.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

withdraw().details: Withdraw accumulated balance for a payee Requirements: - msg.sender must have enough balance in the escrow

regions.details: keep track of every region and its history `region` in bytes32 => season => severity

submissions.details: keep track of submissions `region` in bytes32 => year(season) => Submission (struct defined above)
